#Text=Wikinews interviews Tyan Taylor , Australian goalball player
#Text=Tuesday , September 4 , 2012
#Text=London , England — Yesterday , following a three – nil loss to the United States , Wikinews interviewed Tyan Taylor of Australia 's national goalball team .
#Text=Tyan Taylor , APC publicity shot
#Text=Image : Australian Paralympic Committee ( APC ) .
#Text=The sport was created in 1946 , exclusively for people with a visual disability and , designed to help with the rehabilitation of veterans returning from World War II .
#Text=Play in the Paralympics consists of two twelve-minute periods , with a three minute break between halves .
#Text=Players are blindfolded to ensure all are equally visually handicapped on-court ; and , the game can be stopped to ensure goggles are properly fitted .

#Text=Standing in front of a long goal , they throw the ball at the opposition team 's net who in turn try to block it by listening to the ball , which contains a bell , and using their bodies to prevent the ball from going in .
#Text=The audience is asked to remain silent during play .
#Text=Australia went into their match against the US having lost 1 – 3 to both Japan and Canada .
#Text=They have one game left to play at the London Paralympics against Sweden , who have lost 1 – 5 to the United States , tied Japan 0 – 0 and beaten Canada 2 – 1 .
#Text=Interview transcript
#Text=You guys were n't expecting to qualify .
#Text=The APC [ Australian Paralympic Committee ] has been developing you [ the team , for Rio ] .
#Text=Are you happy with the fact ?
#Text=Do you feel prepared for Rio ?
#Text=Yes , the APC 's , for us , [ planned ] development for Rio .
#Text=That 's what they have as the goal , to make us qualify for Rio .

#Text=So it was a bit of a spanner in the works when we qualified for London ; but , it 's been a massive experience here for us and we have stepped up from qualifying in Sydney in November to where we are now , to God know where we 're going to be for Rio .
#Text=We are all pumped and excited for our team just to keep developing .
#Text=Two of you were dating , or involved with , men on the national team .
#Text=Were they here to watch you ?
#Text=Yes !
#Text=We 've got some of our Aussie men as supporters in the crowd .
#Text=Meica 's husband and Nicole 's husband as well .
#Text=And we have our first mate Robbie , he 's also part of the men 's team .
#Text=They 've been with us and they 've been supporting us since pretty much the start , so we 're doing it on behalf of them as well .
#Text=I know that some of your players look shattered , but do you guys feel the importance ?
#Text=You 're the first Australian team to actually qualify on your own to enter the goalball programme .
#Text=Yeah !
#Text=I mean , some team members tried qualifying for Beijing , unfortunately we were unsuccessful .
#Text=So , I think , some of us having only played the sport for three years and to qualify for London is just a massive achievement .
#Text=We are grabbing every opportunity that we can , and putting everything on the table for each game .
#Text=Are you going to try playing more international competitions , so you do n't have that big lag like you did last time ?

#Text=Hopefully , we get more international competitions , exposure - I suppose - with that , but we 've grown so much with the little amount of international exposure we 've had so I think we 're going to take it and roll with that .
#Text=You 're going to get a medal in Rio ?
#Text=Hopefully we 'll medal !
#Text=We always look for the medals but you never know what is going to happen , so …
#Text=Are you enjoying your time here ?
#Text=Yes !
#Text=Absolutely loving it !
#Text=Awesome !
#Text=The crowd are just insane !
#Text=It 's great .
#Text=We are all having an absolute awesome time .
#Text=Do you have anything else you 'd like to share with with us ?
#Text=Like the [ mismatched ] yellow and green socks as a fashion statement ?
#Text=Yeah !
#Text=Yellow and green socks are … Meica in our team started that fashion .
#Text=So we thought we 'd all .
#Text=The green and the gold .
#Text=On a strategy thing , the US team stood up most of the time , but do you intentionally play differently , or is it just a style preference ?
#Text=For some people it 's a style preference .
#Text=For some … I guess it 's more of a style preference .
#Text=We all stand up between penalties but each to their own really in competitions like this .
#Text=It 's exceptionally fun to watch , having never seen this sport before .
#Text=Thank you very much .
#Text=That 's alright !
#Text=Good luck with Rio !
#Text=Thank you very much .
